sentences: Garrick Olof Ohlsson (born April 3, 1948 in Bronxville, New York) is an American classical pianist.
He is the only American to win first prize in the VIII International Chopin Piano Competition, in 1970.
He was awarded the Avery Fisher Prize in 1994 and received the 1998 University Musical Society Distinguished Artist Award in Ann Arbor, Michigan.
He was awarded the Avery Fisher Prize in 1994 and received the 1998 University Musical Society Distinguished Artist Award in Ann Arbor, Michigan.
Ohlsson has also been nominated for three Grammy Awards, winning one in 2008.
Ohlsson was born in 1948 in White Plains, New York, the only child of a Swedish father and Sicilian-American mother.
In 2005–2006, he toured with the Takács Quartet.
In 2006–2007, he played the opening concert at the Mostly Mozart Festival in New York.
In 2010, he visited Australia and gave concerts in Melbourne.
In 1989, he recorded Busoni's five-movement Piano Concerto in C major, Op.
Shortly after his Chopin competition victory in 1970, he appeared as performing guest on ABC's The Dick Cavett Show on November 14, 1971.

Ohlsson currently lives in San Francisco with his partner, historic preservationist Robert Guter.
